Are you looking to join the Global Leader in production and sales of Consumer Electronics? Do you like to work in a dynamic, challenging and international work environment? Then we have a fantastic opportunity for you to join our best-in-class team as: eStore Project Manager.
Samsung Electronics Europe Logistics (SELS) is the Central European logistics organization of Samsung Electronics based in Delft, The Netherlands. SELS functions as a logistics and financial control tower within Samsung Europe, with a focused role in logistics & supply chain strategy, innovation and governance. SELS has approximately 150 employees located in the Netherlands and Slovakia. 
The D2C TF team governs and develops the logistics operations and distribution networks in Europe (central, local) in cooperation with our logistics service providers (4PL, 3PL) for D2C (Direct to Customer) business. By translating voice of customer and biz requirements into best practice logistics solutions, Initiating advanced logistics innovation, and secure operations excellence.
Role and Responsibilities
We are searching for a new colleague who can be best described as having:
Independent: Able to plan own projects and set priorities        
Responsible: Able to work towards and meet deadlines
Quality: Accurate with an eye for detail
Sensitivity: Strong communicator, cultural awareness
Flexibility: Operate in a fast changing environment
Your main responsibilities will include: 
Streamline process of data collection, reporting and analysis;
Coordinate projects in order to constantly improve activities and process (work smart);
Participate in interdepartmental projects;
Manage project milestone planning and execute progress reporting;
Advice and support Samsung Europe subsidiaries with new solutions and opportunities for logistics operations (productivity, efficiency, risk sensing);
Govern and optimize operations excellence for central and local distribution networks;
Initiate and develop, in close cooperation with our 4PL and 3PL partners, innovative solutions to increase operations service levels and manage costs;
Develop logistics operations and fulfillment network for Samsung online business;
Draft, verify and negotiate operational Terms and Conditions (SLA) with online partners and logistics service providers;
Identify and advise about tailored SCM/logistics solutions and best practices for online business/partnerships to a variety of stakeholders;
Propose process improvement plans to SELS management to increase efficiency, reduce operational cost and improve quality of online business;
Design dedicated warehouse operations ensuring optimum productivity and added value services for online business Including enhancement of workflows and system functionalities (WMS/TMS)
Occasional travel within Europe will be required.
Skills and Qualifications
What we offer:
Working at the Global Leader in Consumer Electronics and in a best-in-class team environment comes with hard work, but we also make it rewarding through:
A competitive base salary depending on your profile;
Annual performance related bonuses (twice per year);
25 holidays (and Good Friday off) and additional loyalty days based on your service period;
Fully compensated health care insurance (extensive coverage);
Well-arranged pension scheme with an extensive employer contribution;
Compensation of your fitness subscription;
Free drinks and fresh fruit at the office;
Employee shop to purchase Samsung products with discount;
Bicycle plan.
Who we are looking for:
Our ideal candidate would suit the following profile:
7+ years working experience in e-commerce and D2C operations;
Experience with(in) the field of Logistics or Supply Chain management (preferred);
Various experience in project management;
Ability to translate complicated requirements into well-defined tasks;
Bachelor degree / Master degree preferable in logistics or related field
Knowledge of warehouse and/or transport management systems (develop, operate);
Knowledge of Front-end system (Hybris, etc.) & ERP system
Experience of operations on Consumer electronics business is strongly preferred
Experience of leading procurement process both in warehouse and last-mile delivery
Ability to clearly translate complicated requirements into easy-to-understand tasks, and to motivate and influence through clear communications in all mediums
Advanced skills in MS Office (Excel, Word and PPT)
Comfortable working across different cultures
Proficient in English (Dutch is not mandatory)
Strong analytical skills;
Furthermore, your approach can be described as flexible and hands-on, which is required in the dynamic, challenging and high performance work environment which Samsung offers. We are looking for a team player who is result and solution oriented and able to work independently. You have excellent communication skills and cultural understanding. Furthermore, you take ownership and accountability in your role.
What’s next:
We hope that we have triggered your interest to join our company. If so, please make sure to apply right away and we will be in touch with you shortly.
